{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, when we remove these criteria from the training data, the model tends to generate responses with artifacts or overlong responses to mislead the rubric verifier into giving a spurious high reward.",
    "In contrast, when these criteria are included, the model learns to generate more coherent and relevant responses that truly satisfy the instructions.",
    "See Section C for a concrete example.",
    "In this paper, we propose a rubric-based learning and evaluation pipeline to improve the IF ability of LLMs.",
    "We release AdvancedIF, a high-quality human-annotated IF benchmark to measure LLMs capability in following complex, multi-turn instructions."
  ]
}